sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I748001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kurt Whittemore
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This section of DNA contains the sequence from 300 base pairs upstream of the Nitrilase/cyanide hydratase and apolipoprotein N-acyltransferase gene to 30 base pairs downstream into the gene from Pseudomonas fluorescens PfO-1. Our hope is that this region of DNA will contain the promoter for the nitrilase gene. At the time that this part was submitted, it was not tested or sequenced yet.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We isolated this segment of DNA from the Pseudomonas fluorescens PfO-1 genome using a PCR reaction.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This section of DNA comes from the Pseudomonas fluorescens PfO-1 genome (NC_007492). The GeneID for the nitrilase gene that we working with is 3715134, and the protein ID for the nitrilase gene is YP_349417.1. We took the region 300 base pairs upstream of the nitrilase gene and 10 base pairs downstream into the gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I723011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Scott Ramsay
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the naturally-occurring (possibly stationary-phase only) promoter for the DntR gene (which encodes the transcriptional regulator DntR) back-to-back with the DntR-regulated promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This does not physically exist as a basic part due to time constraints; it was cloned as part of composite part which incorporates all of the components necessary for expression of a reporter gene under the control of DntR. For this reason, the ends of the supplied sequence may not accurately represent the boundaries of the functional unit.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Cloned from a historical plasmid based on pQF52 carrying genomic sequences from ''Burkholderia cepacia''.
